text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia bruneri is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The shell grows to a length of 5 mm.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations:
Northwest Atlantic Ocean
text.Notes:
Additional information regarding this species:
Distribution: off Rhode Island
